00:26.240 --> 00:29.640
THE EPISODE OF PAUL TO THE ROMANS

00:29.640 --> 00:32.020
KING JAMES' VERSION

00:32.020 --> 00:34.120
CHAPTER XV

00:34.120 --> 00:40.780
We then, that are strong, ought to bear the infirmities of the weak,

00:41.000 --> 00:43.200
and not to please ourselves.

00:43.680 --> 00:49.220
Let every one of us please his neighbor, for his good to edification.

00:49.620 --> 00:54.600
For even Christ pleased not himself, but, as it is written,

00:54.600 --> 00:59.140
the reproaches of them that reproached thee fell on me.

00:59.560 --> 01:05.300
For whatsoever things were written for time were written for our learning,

01:05.520 --> 01:10.320
that we, through patience and comfort of the scriptures, might have hope.

01:10.780 --> 01:16.460
Now the God of patience and consolation grant you to be like-minded,

01:16.920 --> 01:20.260
one toward another according to Christ Jesus,

01:20.260 --> 01:24.800
that ye may with one mind and one mouth glorify God,

01:25.200 --> 01:28.660
even the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.

01:29.200 --> 01:36.180
Wherefore receive ye one another as Christ also received us to the glory of God.

01:36.540 --> 01:41.400
Now I say that Jesus Christ was a minister of the circumcision,

01:41.740 --> 01:47.680
for the truth of God to confirm the promises made unto the fathers,

01:48.580 --> 01:52.960
and that the Gentiles might glorify God for his mercy,

01:53.440 --> 01:54.660
as it is written,

01:55.100 --> 01:59.180
for this cause I will confess to thee among the Gentiles,

01:59.520 --> 02:01.580
and sing unto thy name.

02:01.860 --> 02:03.360
And again he saith,

02:03.740 --> 02:06.600
Rejoice ye Gentiles with his people.

02:06.900 --> 02:10.320
And again, praise the Lord all ye Gentiles,

02:11.000 --> 02:13.640
and laud him all ye people.

02:14.020 --> 02:16.120
And again Isaiah saith,

02:16.120 --> 02:18.700
There shall be a root of Jesse,

02:19.200 --> 02:26.020
and he that shall rise to reign over the Gentiles in him shall the Gentiles trust.

02:26.480 --> 02:31.220
Now the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace,

02:31.680 --> 02:36.940
in believing that ye may abound in hope through the power of the Holy Ghost.

02:37.200 --> 02:42.140
And I myself also am persuaded of you, my brethren,

02:42.140 --> 02:45.120
that ye also are full of goodness,

02:45.140 --> 02:50.940
filled with all knowledge able also to admonish one another.

02:51.320 --> 02:52.660
Nevertheless, brethren,

02:53.180 --> 02:57.140
I have written the more boldly unto you in some sort,

02:57.500 --> 03:02.900
as putting you in mind because of the grace that is given to me of God,

03:03.080 --> 03:07.900
that I should be the minister of Jesus Christ to the Gentiles,

03:08.160 --> 03:10.420
ministering the gospel of God,

03:10.420 --> 03:15.680
that the offering up of the Gentiles might be acceptable,

03:16.100 --> 03:19.200
being sanctified by the Holy Ghost.

03:19.760 --> 03:21.400
I have therefore,

03:21.760 --> 03:28.640
whereof I make glory through Jesus Christ in those things which pertain to God,

03:28.800 --> 03:35.520
for I will not dare to speak of any of those things which Christ hath not wrought by me

03:35.520 --> 03:39.620
to make the Gentiles obedient by word and deed.

03:39.620 --> 03:44.740
Through mighty signs and wonders by the power of the Spirit of God,

03:44.920 --> 03:50.800
so that from Jerusalem and round about unto Euryseum,

03:51.220 --> 03:55.400
I have fully preached the gospel of Christ.

03:55.840 --> 03:59.520
Yea, so have I strived to preach the gospel,

03:59.940 --> 04:02.000
not where Christ was named,

04:02.440 --> 04:07.000
lest I should build upon another man's foundation.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.440
But, as it is written,

04:09.900 --> 04:12.280
to whom he was not spoken of,

04:12.500 --> 04:13.480
they shall see,

04:13.980 --> 04:17.120
and they that have not heard shall understand,

04:17.580 --> 04:23.340
for which cause also I have been much hindered from coming to you.

04:23.660 --> 04:26.920
But now, having no more place in these parts,

04:27.300 --> 04:32.400
and having a great desire these many years to come unto you,

04:32.400 --> 04:35.820
when soever I take my journey into Spain,

04:36.200 --> 04:37.980
I will come to you.

04:38.260 --> 04:41.020
For I trust to see you in my journey,

04:41.300 --> 04:46.360
and to be brought on my way through the word by you,

04:46.600 --> 04:51.300
if first I be somewhat filled with your company.

04:51.620 --> 04:56.440
But now I go unto Jerusalem to minister unto the saints,

04:56.780 --> 05:01.880
for it hath pleased them of Macedonia and Achaia

05:01.880 --> 05:05.400
to make a certain contribution for the poor saints,

05:05.940 --> 05:07.380
which are at Jerusalem.

05:07.800 --> 05:09.740
It hath pleased them verily,

05:10.040 --> 05:12.320
and their debtors they are.

05:12.480 --> 05:18.300
For if the Gentiles have been made partakers of their spiritual things,

05:18.720 --> 05:24.020
their duty is also to minister unto them in carnal things.

05:24.520 --> 05:26.820
When therefore I have performed this,

05:27.020 --> 05:29.180
and have sealed to them this fruit,

05:29.180 --> 05:32.540
I will come by you into Spain.

05:33.040 --> 05:36.680
And I am sure that when I come unto you,

05:36.840 --> 05:41.820
I shall come in the fullness of the blessing of the gospel of Christ.

05:42.320 --> 05:43.940
Now I beseech you, brethren,

05:44.340 --> 05:46.400
for the Lord Jesus Christ's sake,

05:46.700 --> 05:48.760
and for the love of the Spirit,

05:49.180 --> 05:54.840
that you strive together with me in your prayers to God for me,

05:54.840 --> 06:00.540
that I may be delivered from them that do not believe in Judea,

06:00.560 --> 06:07.300
and that my service which I have for Jerusalem may be accepted of the saints,

06:07.600 --> 06:12.360
that I may come unto you with joy by the will of God,

06:12.480 --> 06:15.760
and may with you be refreshed.

06:16.120 --> 06:20.320
Now, the God of peace be with you all.

06:20.340 --> 06:21.060
Amen.

06:21.960 --> 06:23.540
Chapter 16

06:23.540 --> 06:27.360
I commend unto you, Phoebe, our sister,

06:27.740 --> 06:29.820
which is a servant of the church,

06:30.520 --> 06:32.860
which is at Sincrea,

06:33.240 --> 06:37.920
that ye receive her in the Lord as becomeeth saints,

06:37.960 --> 06:45.040
and that ye assist her in whatsoever business she hath need of you,

06:45.180 --> 06:50.240
for she hath been a succorer of many and of myself also.

06:50.240 --> 06:54.840
Greet Priscilla and Aquila, my helpers in Christ Jesus,

06:55.780 --> 07:00.160
who have for my life laid down their own necks,

07:00.360 --> 07:02.540
unto whom not only I give thanks,

07:02.800 --> 07:06.320
but also all the churches of the Gentiles.

07:06.780 --> 07:11.800
Likewise, greet the church that is in their house.

07:11.800 --> 07:15.780
Salute, my well-beloved, Epinetus,

07:16.160 --> 07:22.020
who is the firstfruits of Achaea, unto Christ.

07:22.420 --> 07:26.020
Greet Mary, who bestowed much labor on us.

07:26.700 --> 07:31.120
Salute Andronicus and Jania, my kinsmen,

07:31.240 --> 07:33.100
and my fellow prisoners,

07:33.540 --> 07:39.740
who are of note among the apostles who also were in Christ before me.

07:39.740 --> 07:44.320
Greet Amplius, my beloved, in the Lord.

07:44.740 --> 07:47.460
Salute Urbain, our helper in Christ.

07:48.140 --> 07:50.440
And Statis, my beloved.

07:51.120 --> 07:54.060
Salute Appelles, approved in Christ.

07:55.080 --> 07:59.860
Salute them which are of Aristobulus's household.

08:01.160 --> 08:04.060
Salute Herodion, my kinsmen.

08:04.340 --> 08:08.380
Greet them that be of the household of Narcissus,

08:08.380 --> 08:10.520
which are in the Lord.

08:11.000 --> 08:16.880
Salute Trifina and Trifossa, who labor in the Lord.

08:17.280 --> 08:23.000
Salute the beloved Percissus, which labored much in the Lord.

08:23.420 --> 08:28.380
Salute Rufus, chosen in the Lord, and his mother and mine.

08:30.520 --> 08:37.000
Salute Asencritus, Philegon, Hermas, Petrobus, Hermes,

08:37.000 --> 08:40.720
and the brethren which are with them.

08:41.120 --> 08:46.560
Salute Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister,

08:46.960 --> 08:51.100
and Olympus and all the saints which are with them.

08:51.700 --> 08:55.400
Salute one another with an holy kiss.

08:56.020 --> 08:58.880
The churches of Christ salute you.

08:59.340 --> 09:05.120
Now I beseech you, brethren, mark them which cause divisions and offenses

09:05.120 --> 09:09.940
contrary to the doctrine which ye have learned, and avoid them.

09:10.920 --> 09:16.240
For they that are such serve not our Lord Jesus Christ, but their own belly,

09:16.680 --> 09:22.100
and by good words and fair speeches deceive the hearts of the simple.

09:23.080 --> 09:27.200
For your obedience is come abroad unto all men.

09:27.440 --> 09:30.000
I am glad therefore on your behalf.

09:30.000 --> 09:37.880
But yet I would have you wise unto that which is good and simple concerning evil.

09:38.560 --> 09:43.100
And the God of peace shall bruise Satan under your feet shortly.

09:43.760 --> 09:49.320
The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you. Amen.

09:50.200 --> 09:58.360
Timotheus, my work fellow, and Lucius and Jason, and so Sipater, my kinsmen, salute you.

09:58.360 --> 10:05.240
I, Tertius, who wrote this epistle, salute you and the Lord.

10:05.680 --> 10:10.980
Gaius, mine host, and of the whole church, saluteth you.

10:11.360 --> 10:15.600
Arrestus, the chamberlain of the city, saluteth you.

10:16.000 --> 10:23.400
And Quartus, a brother, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.

10:23.400 --> 10:35.380
Now to him that is of power to establish you according to my gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ,

10:35.840 --> 10:43.540
according to the revelation of the mystery which was kept secret since the world began,

10:43.880 --> 10:49.380
but now is made manifest, and by the scriptures of the prophets,

10:49.380 --> 10:58.800
according to the commandment of the everlasting God made known to all nations for the obedience of faith.

10:59.300 --> 11:08.300
To God, only wise, be glory through Jesus Christ forever. Amen.

11:09.740 --> 11:17.420
End of chapter 16, reading by Simon Wainwright.

11:17.420 --> 11:25.540
End of the epistle of Paul to the Romans, King James Version.

